   "source": [
    "# Pipeline 1: Donor Lapse Risk Classifier\n",
    "**Organization:** The Lighthouse  \n",
    "**Author:** Michael  \n",
    "**Date:** April 2026  \n",
    "**Pipeline type:** Binary Classification (Predictive + Explanatory)  \n",
    "**Tables used:** supporters.csv, donations.csv  \n",
    "**Model deployed:** Gradient Boosting Classifier  \n",
    "**Deployment:** score.py → donor_risk_scores.json → API endpoint → Admin Dashboard watchlist"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f536acab",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Section 1: Problem Framing — Donor Lapse Risk Classifier\n",
    "\n",
    "## Business Problem\n",
    "\n",
    "Our partner nonprofit has approximately **60 active supporters** — donors, volunteers,\n",
    "in-kind contributors, and social media advocates. Of these, **15 have already gone\n",
    "inactive** (a 25% lapse rate). The organization has no dedicated marketing or data\n",
    "team; the executive director manages all donor relationships personally. Without an\n",
    "early-warning system, lapsing donors slip through the cracks until it is too late to\n",
    "re-engage them.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Why Classification?\n",
    "\n",
    "We frame this as a **binary classification** problem: given a supporter's donation\n",
    "history and profile, predict whether they are **lapsed** (`is_lapsed = 1`) or\n",
    "**active** (`is_lapsed = 0`). The model's predicted probabilities then serve as a\n",
    "continuous **risk score** for ranking donors on a watchlist.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Two Models, Two Goals\n",
    "\n",
    "We intentionally build **two** models rather than choosing one:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Model | Goal | Strength |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| **Logistic Regression** | *Explanation* — understand **why** donors lapse | Coefficients map directly to human-readable risk reasons |\n",
    "| **Gradient Boosting** | *Prediction* — maximize out-of-sample accuracy | Captures non-linear interactions; powers the ranked watchlist |\n",
    "\n",
    "The logistic regression tells staff *\"donors acquired through Word of Mouth are 3× more\n",
    "likely to lapse\"* — that insight shapes acquisition strategy. The gradient boosting model\n",
    "tells the system *\"score Rosa at 0.84 and rank her #2 on the watchlist\"* — that drives\n",
    "operational outreach.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Success Metrics\n",
    "\n",
    "Because our classes are imbalanced (75% active / 25% lapsed), raw accuracy is\n",
    "misleading. Our primary metrics are:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Balanced Accuracy** — average of recall on each class, not dominated by the majority\n",
    "- **ROC AUC** — measures ranking quality across all probability thresholds\n",
    "\n",
    "Secondary metrics: **F1 score** (harmonic mean of precision and recall) and\n",
    "**log loss** (penalizes confident wrong predictions).\n",
    "\n",
    "## Cost of Errors\n",
    "\n",
    "| Error Type | Business Impact | Cost |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| **False Negative** (miss a lapsing donor) | Lost relationship, lost future revenue, donor feels ignored | **High** |\n",
    "| **False Positive** (flag an active donor) | One unnecessary but friendly phone call | **Low** |\n",
    "\n",
    "Because false negatives are far more costly, we **tune for recall** — we would rather\n",
    "make a few extra phone calls than miss a donor who is drifting away."
   ]
  },
  {
