   "source": [
    "## EDA Findings\n",
    "\n",
    "The exploratory analysis reveals several useful — but noisy — signals for predicting donor lapse.\n",
    "**`lifetime_value_php`** and **`total_donation_count`** are the strongest numeric separators:\n",
    "lapsed donors contributed substantially less total value and gave fewer times overall, which aligns\n",
    "with the intuition that shallow engagement predicts disengagement.\n",
    "\n",
    "**`gap_ratio`** is weaker than expected — lapsed donors average roughly 1.64 vs 1.53 for active\n",
    "donors — meaning *both* groups tend to exceed their personal average gap, just to different degrees.\n",
    "This suggests gap_ratio alone is not a clean decision boundary, but it may add value in combination\n",
    "with other features.\n",
    "\n",
    "Among categorical features, **SkillsContributors** (67% lapse rate) and **PartnerOrganizations**\n",
    "(50%) stand out as the highest-risk supporter types, while **MonetaryDonors** lapse at a lower rate.\n",
    "Acquisition channel shows moderate separation, with some channels clustering well above the 25.4%\n",
    "baseline.\n",
    "\n",
    "It is important to be honest about scale: with **59 rows and only 15 positive cases**, all of these\n",
    "patterns are present but inherently noisy. Small-sample fluctuations can easily produce misleading\n",
    "effect sizes, which is why we rely on cross-validated metrics rather than single-split results."
   ]
  },
