    "# Section 3: Modeling & Feature Selection\n",
    "\n",
    "We build two models with distinct purposes:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Logistic Regression** — our *explanatory* model. Its standardized coefficients tell us\n",
    "   which features drive lapse risk and in which direction. These coefficients power the\n",
    "   plain-language \"risk reason\" cards shown to staff (e.g., *\"147 days since last gift —\n",
    "   3.9× their usual gap\"*). We use L1/L2 regularization to handle collinearity among our\n",
    "   24 features and `class_weight='balanced'` to compensate for the 75/25 imbalance.\n",
    "\n",
    "2. **Gradient Boosting** — our *predictive* model. It captures non-linear interactions\n",
    "   (e.g., a donor with low lifetime value AND high gap_ratio may be at much higher risk\n",
    "   than either feature alone would suggest). Its predicted probabilities power the ranked\n",
    "   watchlist. We tune hyperparameters via randomized search to avoid overfitting on 59 rows."
   ]
  },
