   "source": [
    "## Business Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "Looking at the confusion matrices in business terms: every **false negative** represents a\n",
    "donor the organization would fail to reach out to — a lost relationship and potentially\n",
    "thousands of pesos in future revenue. Every **false positive** represents one unnecessary\n",
    "but friendly phone call — a low-cost mistake that might even strengthen the relationship.\n",
    "\n",
    "With only 12 test observations (3 lapsed, 9 active), individual test-set numbers bounce\n",
    "around considerably. The more stable cross-validation results give a better picture of\n",
    "expected performance. Both models achieve reasonable balanced accuracy given the severe\n",
    "data constraint (59 rows, 15 positives).\n",
    "\n",
    "For **deployment**, we recommend the **Gradient Boosting** model for watchlist scoring because\n",
    "its predicted probabilities tend to rank donors more effectively (higher AUC). However, the\n",
    "**Logistic Regression** model remains essential for generating the plain-language risk-reason\n",
    "cards that staff see on each donor's profile — its coefficients provide the \"why\" behind each\n",
    "risk score.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Honest limitation:** With a dataset this small, model performance estimates have wide\n",
    "confidence intervals. As the organization accumulates more supporter data over time, the\n",
    "models should be retrained periodically. Even a doubling of the dataset (to ~120 supporters)\n",
    "would substantially stabilize both the feature importance rankings and the out-of-sample\n",
    "accuracy estimates."
   ]
  },
